# ABC/XYZ formula descriptions
ABCFormulaTitle = ABC Classification
ABCFormulaDesc = Products ranked by cumulative revenue contribution. Class A = top %s%% of revenue | Class B = next %s%% | Class C = remaining %s%%
XYZFormulaTitle = XYZ Classification
XYZFormulaDesc = Products classified by demand variability (Coefficient of Variation). X: CV <= %s (stable) | Y: CV <= %s (variable) | Z: CV > %s (erratic)
ABCXYZFormulaTitle = ABC-XYZ Combined Matrix
ABCXYZFormulaDesc = Combines revenue importance (ABC) with demand predictability (XYZ). AX = high-value stable demand, CZ = low-value erratic demand
DeadStockFormulaTitle = Dead Stock Detection
DeadStockFormulaDesc = Products with zero stock movements in the last %s days despite having stock on hand
SlowStockFormulaTitle = Slow Moving Stock
SlowStockFormulaDesc = Products with fewer than %s stock movements in the last %s days
StockAgingFormulaTitle = Stock Aging Analysis
StockAgingFormulaDesc = Days since last inbound (receipt) movement per product per warehouse. Older stock = higher carrying cost
StockoutRiskFormulaTitle = Stockout Risk Score
StockoutRiskFormulaDesc = Risk Score = Current Stock / (Avg Daily Consumption x Lead Time). Score below %s = at risk of stockout

